Package fr.cs.group13.myVelib.core.user

Class User

java.lang.Object
fr.cs.group13.myVelib.core.user.User
public class User extends Object
The User class represents a user of the bike rental system. This class includes details about the user and methods to rent and return a bike.

    • returnBicycle

      public double returnBicycle()
      Returns the bicycle to a location outside of any docking station (on the street). The GPS coordinates of the bicycle are assigned as the current coordinates of the user.
      Returns:
      The charge for the rental.
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if the user doesn't have a bicycle.

    • returnBicycle

      public double returnBicycle(ParkingSlot slot)
      Returns the bicycle to the specified parking slot.
      Parameters:
      slot - The parking slot where the bicycle is being returned.
      Returns:
      The charge for the rental.
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if the user doesn't have a bicycle.

    • returnBicycle

      public double returnBicycle(double duration)
      This method allows the user to return a bike to a random place which is not a slot.
      Parameters:
      duration - The duration of the bike ride in minutes.
      Returns:
      The charge for the rental.
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if the user isn't currently renting a bike
